= Webdoc

== Instruction for development installation

Dependencies:

- Ruby 1.8.6
- RubyGems 1.3.6
- Rails 2.3.5
- Rake
- SQlite3 (on Windows, install sqlite3 and ruby gem for mswin32 from http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=254)

Run in working repository:

  sudo gem install bundler
  sudo bundle install

Create a sym link to app/javascripts

 On MacOSX or Linux fom the public/app folder do
   ln -s ../../app/javascripts/ javascripts
 On Windows vista or 7 from the public/app folder do
   mklink /D javascripts ..\app\javascripts
 On Windows XP sym link does not exist and you must modify config/assets.yml with
   package_assets: always
 
   
If all tests pass, you can work on a big new feature ;-)


== Plugins

== Webdoc Fork source code

Here is a new way to get the code from webdoc. It will be easier for us to get your update and
easier for you to get our update.
Please work in the branch master, it will be easier for us to get your update (the send merge request message will contain your new commit)

you'll find the new repo on assembla here :

https://www.assembla.com/code/webdoc-fork-xb/git/nodes?rev=master

-- Get the code locally:

git clone git@git.assembla.com:webdoc-fork-xb.git

-- To get our latest update :

git pull git@git.assembla.com:webdoc dev


To send us your update, you have to:

-- Push your code to assembla

git push origin master

-- then login into assembla and go here :

https://www.assembla.com/code/webdoc-fork-xb/git/forks

and clic on 'send a merge request'

Fill the form and send it.

